==English==

===Interjection===
'''boo'''

# '''boo!''' An [[loud]] [[exclamation]] intended to [[scare]] someone, especially a child.  Usually used when one has been [[hidden]] from the [[victim]] and then suddenly [[appear]]ed [[unexpectedly]].
# '''boo.''' A word used [[ironically]] in a situation where one might have scared someone, but said someone was not scared.  Not said as loudly as in definition 1.
# '''boo.''' A word used by someone who is inherently [[scary]], such as a [[bully]] or a [[vampire]], to make a weaker person who is [[scared stiff]] [[flee]].  Usually used quietly, as with definition 2.
# '''boo!''' An exclamation used by a member of an [[audience]], as at a stage [[play]] or sports [[game]], to indicate [[derision]] or [[disapproval]] of what has just occurred.

